<!-- SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Modern estate living for young families in the outer west.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Ellen Grove sits approximately 17 kilometres south-west of the Brisbane CBD, bordered by Forest Lake, Doolandella, Richlands, Inala and Durack. It is a suburb built predominantly through the 1990s and 2000s as a modern residential estate, and the housing stock reflects that: neat brick and tile homes on usable blocks with established gardens, estate streetscapes and the practical community infrastructure that comes with planned development. Young families are the dominant buyer here, and they are buying on a clear brief around space, schooling options and motorway access.
    </p>
