<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work across Brisbane's outer western corridor and understand the buyer profiles that turn up in Ellen Grove. Young families with pre-approvals, first home buyers comparing Ellen Grove against Forest Lake and Richlands, and investors drawn by the consistent rental demand are the three groups every vendor needs to understand before launching a campaign here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Ellen Grove's proximity to Forest Lake's major retail hub on Forest Lake Boulevard, the Ipswich Motorway and the Springfield Central rail corridor makes it attractive to buyers who need practical commute options. Families priced out of Forest Lake's newer estate stock regularly look to Ellen Grove as the next step, bringing motivated buyer energy that a well-run campaign can convert. Properties with flat, usable blocks, good internal layouts and clean estate presentation consistently attract the strongest buyer competition in this corridor.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
